<br>
We're in that awkward phase where we've lost several 50+ people because of a lack of support for epics, raids, PoP groups, etc.  At one point, we enforced a no alts until lvl 45 policy, to try and get people to a closer level, but this caused several low level people to leave.  In order to accomodate everyone, our &quot;raids&quot; (using the term loosely) have been to zones like Tower of the Frozen Shadow, Lower Guk, SolB, Hollowshade.  Since we have such a broad range of levels, though, no one gets exp, there's little loot in these zones, and its trivial content for the upper level peeps.  Anyway, enough with the history.<br>
<br>
Can anyone share some advice on how to get through this stage?  I don't want to see the guild fail, as I've invested a lot of energy in it, and have made many friends.  I see a few options, all of which have drawbacks:<br>
1) tighten up recruiting, and only accept people above a certain level (45 or so?)<br>
2) Have guild powerleveling nights, where people park themselves in TD and I quad spirocs until my eyes bleed.<br>
3) Hook up with a higher level guild and become their junior partner.<br>
4) Beg and plead for people to stop playing alts and to level their mains<br>
<br>
Anyway, I'd appreciate any insight or advice. <p>Willain of Xev<br>
